node.text:
Easier said than done, I couldn’t agree more but together I believe we can commit to starting conversations around our mental health that celebrate vulnerability and honesty. 
How many times has someone said “how are you” even someone you trust 100% and you say “I’m fine” it’s a toxic reflex so many of us have. When have you ever answered to be honest, pretty down..
We have this idea in our heads that maybe “people don’t want to listen” or “we don’t want to bring others down” but truthfully the right people will listen & hold space to hear you. 
I was always someone that preferred the “I’m fine” even to my bf, he hated it knowing I wasn’t fine most the time and it wasn’t until I embraced honest conversation that true healing came. 

Vulnerability for women & men is a superpower.

If you aren’t okay I’m going to be on my DM all day answering as many people as I can but please know @ruokday is here for you and @lifelineaustralia is always at the end of the phone.

You are appreciated,

Love always,
G #RUOK #MENTALHEALTHMATTERS

node.title: RUOK? Starting honest conversations around mental health ☀️

node.text:
Taking my time when I’m getting ready is one of my favourite forms of self care, doing all the little things that make me feel fresh ✨
Teeth whitening isn’t something I do all the time but when I feel like I need it, I drink a lot of tea and tumeric based foods so having @hismile handy has always been helpful. 
I’ve used Hismile for almost 4 years, I first got it when I was travelling like crazy. Without time for dentist chairs, I always had something easy to use where ever I was on a plane or just at home ✨
Their new formulation is clinically proven to whiten without sensitivity, the reason I’m excited about it is because it’s peroxide free which means less nasties and more bright smiles! 🌻 
#HismilePartner #SmileCare #HiSmile #Smilemore
🎥 by @ihatekuz

node.text:
Tonights flow ready for its yogi rookie debut. I made a choice this afternoon, stay stressed or take 10 mins for myself, I chose myself, I chose strength in moving my body, I chose a moment of calm,  I chose those breaths of fresh air, I chose me. To me an empowered woman is a woman that grants herself permission to do what’s right for her. 🥂
For this international women’s day @alo will donate $1 to Catalyst inc, a non profit built to accelerate women into leadership roles with every post we share!
I nominate these inspiring ladies I miss so much @aijamayrock @audreylittie @linzheppner to share what empowers them & tag 3 women that inspire them too. ❤️

node.title: Tonight’s 5 minute flow, give yourself permission to do something for you🌙

node.text:
Hey guys,

Here’s the LIVE from this morning with the lovely Joyce from @wildspiritfragrances 🧡 She’s a self confessed “sensitive to everything soul” & so I wanted to chat to her on why conscious fragrance choices made such a big difference to us & our health. 🌻

We cover; - our favourite fragrance / what I wear
- affordability
- ingredients to avoid
- how scents influence mood
- why @wildspiritfragrances was created with essential oils & without nasties like Suphates, Parabens & Dyes. 
Ask me anything I’ll be on the comments below!

GG 🌈

node.title: Fragrances aren’t created equal ft expert Joyce Lanigan of Wild Spirit ✨

node.text:
Helloooo fam,

No one has ever fulfilled their self care routine and felt worse after, *you only regret the self care you didn’t do* so take a little extra time for you today. 
This video is my self care / beauty routine I try and do once a week or every second week. I prep for my tan, face mask, hair mask & pop on a fresh coat of @bondisands ❤️
I hope you enjoy the video and are inspired to take 5 for you! Shop the range at @Walgreens 🇺🇸
GG 🌻 x

node.text:
Health care workers, teachers, support staff, carers, supermarket & pharmacy employees, warehouse staff, petrol station attendees, council workers, police officers, couriers & delivery workers, scientists, charity’s & community organisations, every person that isn’t at home because their incredible work is allowing the world to be, truly thank you. 
How lucky we are to have you all in this situation, check in with the elderly you know, maybe they live across from you or are friends of friends, I miss my nan too but we’ve got her working out the FaceTime! 🎉🌻💛 xxx

node.text:
It took me 26 years to realise that my biggest catalyst for success was every failure that came before it 🙏🏽
“Your first is often your worst and at best a test” I heard that on @jayshetty ‘s podcast the other day and it rang through so true. To every soul reading this, fail and fail again, your biggest idol probably failed a 100 times before reaching where you see them now! Our social constructs demonize failure as an “embarrassment” are you really scared to fail or just scared of who’s watching? 
Every failed business, every failed “big” idea, every failed exam, every failure in my health, every failure in relationships lead me to my greatest success’s.
That failed exam made me realise I was forcing something that didn’t actually make me happy & to try a new life path, now I study what I love.
That failed business, made me study what I needed to create an aligned one.
That failed relationship taught me what I didn’t want in a relationship and lead me to what I did want.
Every failure on my health journey, every medicine, pill and prescription that didn’t work taught me to dive deeper and gain the skills necessary to help myself.
Failure is the greatest lesson in life, the most humbling experience and opportunity for growth. Don’t shy away from it, go for it!
All you have to lose is to fail and gain understanding & alignment in your life that no textbook could ever teach you. ❤️❤️
Free in @alo #Fearlessinfailure

node.text:
Easier said than done, I couldn’t agree more but together I believe we can commit to starting conversations around our mental health that celebrate vulnerability and honesty. 
How many times has someone said “how are you” even someone you trust 100% and you say “I’m fine” it’s a toxic reflex so many of us have. When have you ever answered to be honest, pretty down..
We have this idea in our heads that maybe “people don’t want to listen” or “we don’t want to bring others down” but truthfully the right people will listen & hold space to hear you. 
I was always someone that preferred the “I’m fine” even to my bf, he hated it knowing I wasn’t fine most the time and it wasn’t until I embraced honest conversation that true healing came. 

Vulnerability for women & men is a superpower.

If you aren’t okay I’m going to be on my DM all day answering as many people as I can but please know @ruokday is here for you and @lifelineaustralia is always at the end of the phone.

You are appreciated,

Love always,
G #RUOK #MENTALHEALTHMATTERS

node.text:
In need of a new book? 🌈
A few of my favs 🦋 Comment which you would like to read & I’ll post it to you x

#1 Women who run with the wolves by Clarissa Pinkola Estes
It takes a minute to really get into but once I was in, I was gone and finished reading in a week. Ignite your wild woman 🦋 This book was given to me by @montanalower when I was having a hard time so I think it’s time for me do the same, I’ll randomly pick one of you, comment book #1 🌻

#2 Count down by @drshannaswan 
This backed by science book shares Dr Swans research into declining fertility and its relation to endocrine disrupters in our environment. She explored how the male sperm count has dropped more than 50% in the last 50 years & how to reverse it.
I recommend this to all health conscious men & anyone interested in reproductive health & environmental toxins.

#3 Ego is the enemy by Ryan Holiday 
Ryan explores how your ego plays into every area of your life, how it limits your ability to act from a place of truth & alignment with yourself. I found it interesting given the social media, self promotional world we’re living in.

#4 Dear girl by @aijamayrock 💕
One of my favorite books to pick up and flick to any page, I feel that dear girl always serves me what I need to hear, it’s like having a big sister in your pocket. Dear girl would be one of my favorite poetry books. 
I’m sharing this book with one of you because I feel there’s so many women that could do with a pick me up right now & I truly believe books are made to be shared, just comment #4 🦋

#5 The secret by Rhonda Byrne 
You’ve probably read it, I love to refer back to it when I need a bit of a reminder to trust in myself & focus on attracting what it is I align with. 

#6 You are enough by @cassiemendozajones 
I love that Cassie uses a practical approach to work out what’s limiting your self worth & how can you work through it & thrive.🌻

#7 Breathe by @mrjamesnestor 
Also going to post this book to one of you that needs help with breath work (anxiety & anything else) 
This book changed my life, dads life & most of my family. Breath is the most underrated, under utilized healing tool we have available to us.
G x
#Bookclub

node.text:
What I eat in a day, lock down addition ✨ 
Remember when the world feels heavy, focus on vibrant, nourishing, light foods & when you feel a little flat, under the weather or just need a pick me up opt for wholesome foods like soups & stews. Most of all, ditch diets & listen to your intuition… what is your body craving? 🌻 #Intuitiveeating #food #foodismedicine

node.text:
My last big flare up > today! 💪🏾❤️
My new YouTube video is live, how I cured myself of Rosacea using natural methods & a 4 step approach. 
If I can do it, I believe so can you 🦋 
Tip; one of them has everything to do with my emotions… 🤯
If you are after more help with Rosacea diagnosis, understanding what type you have or just advice / questions feel free to refer to my previous post a little further down on my feed ✨
Please always refer to your health care professional when looking to diagnose and/or treat any skin condition ⚡️
I’m just here to share my journey in the hopes it helps some of you, please make sure to like, subscribe & let me know how you go, I don’t monetize my website or my YouTube so please share the love around ❤️
Love, G xx

node.text:
Tom had to drag me out of bed this morning but I am so glad he did. 🦋
Safe to stay I’m still not someone that likes the cold.. 🧊 
I’ve been unmotivated lately, up and down like a yo-yo but I feel like we can all relate to that. 
Be kind to yourself, the waves of emotions & uncomfortable feelings, feel them and try to let them pass 🙏🏽
Please know; you are loved & you are needed. xx
